transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, uh, I got a message that a doctor keeps trying to get me on cash.

Speaker 1: And it's been going on now for two weeks.

Speaker 2: Can you say that one more time, sir? I couldn't hear you, I'm sorry about that.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm calling because I get these text messages that a doctor's trying to reach me.

Speaker 2: Okay, what was your first and last name, sir?

Speaker 1: Uh, Jerome Dorsey.

Speaker 2: Okay, Mr. Dorsey, I can figure this out for you, no problem.

Speaker 1: Give me just a second.

Speaker 2: Oh, I see what's going on here, Mr. Dorsey.

Speaker 1: It's because of the state you live in.

Speaker 2: They said they've been trying to call you, call you, call you, but they haven't been able to reach you.

Speaker 1: Are you at 302-293-2437?

Speaker 2: I'm going to call, if they call me and it rings, I will hear it.

Speaker 1: I'm going to tell them to call you, call you, call you, call you, call you all day today.

Speaker 2: Just keep call, call, call, call, calling.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm here.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay, I'm going to tell them.

Speaker 1: Alright, thank you, thank you, Mr. Dorsey.
